sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1472612
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This translational unit is composed of delta9, delta 12 and delta 15 desaturase genes with RBS for each of them. Desaturase introduces a cis-carbon double bond to fatty acid carbon chain. ∆ 9 desaturase introduce double bond to stearic acid at the carbon 9 position to produce oleic acid. ∆12 desaturase introduce double bond at carbon 12 of oleic acid so to produce linolenic acid. At the end, ∆15 desaturase convert linolenic acid into alpha-linolenic acid by adding a double bond at carbon 15.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Choi hiu Ying, LEE Cheuk Lam, Tse Yui Shing, Yeung Sin Yu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All the desaturase sequences are derived from the Synechocystis sp. but optimised for the expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The desaturase genes in plasmids were introduced into E. coli for amplification. The final construct includes iGEM provided RBS (BBa_B0034).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1027002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Delta 12 Desaturase, optimised for expression in Escherichia coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This enzyme is obtained from the gene Oleic acid desaturase (ode).The gene is obtained from Synechocystis sp., a cyanobacterium and introduced in the E.coli. It is a trans-membrane enzyme, involved in the biosynthesis of C18:2 from C18:1. C18:2 corresponds to Linolenic acid. The delta 12 desaturase introduces a second cis carbon double bond on the 12th carbon in C18:1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Harrison, Lorna Hepworth, Vun Hiang Tan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Produced synthetically based on protein sequence from Synechocystis sp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimization for expression in E coli

The delta 9 desaturase introduces cis carbon double bond on the 9th carbon in C18:0.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1472610
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence encoded for the delta15 desaturase. The gene is from Synechocystis sp. and optimised for the expression in E. coli. During the fatty acid conversion process, delta 15 desaturase catalyses the conversion of linolenic acid (18:2) into alpha-Linolenic acid, ALA (18:3) by adding a cis-doube bond at carbon 15.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Choi hiu Ying, LEE Cheuk Lam, Tse Yui Shing, Yeung Sin Yu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The amino acid sequence of delta 15 desaturase is derived from Synechocystis sp. but codon optimised for the expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The enzyme cut site must be designed according to iGEM prefix and suffix requirements.
